history.content: No, Cal Central does not behave any differently in summer session to the best of my knowledge and will never enroll you in two conflicting classes.  Since CS160 has a waitlist as large as the class capacity, there is no chance that a conflict override would be granted.  Students withouth conflicts will take any space that might be created through attrition.

I am currently enrolled in EE16A over the summer and am on the waitlist for CS160 which has a conflict. Will Cal Central automatically move me from the waitlist when I get into the class or will I need to override the conflict somehow? Don't see an option for manual override so wanted to ask! Thank you.
history.subject: Summer Class Conflict
